some sort of golden age,

00:44:43.470 --> 00:44:46.410
the other people being--
(Leon laughs)

00:44:46.410 --> 00:44:50.030
- Well, as a graduate student at Columbia,

00:44:50.030 --> 00:44:51.590
we had a button made

00:44:53.340 --> 00:44:56.443
which we wore occasionally called Not Yet.

00:44:56.443 --> 00:44:58.460
(audience laughs)
And that's because

00:44:58.460 --> 00:45:01.890
the faculty at Columbia were
loaded with Nobel Prizes.

00:45:01.890 --> 00:45:04.810
There was Rabi, there was Townes.

00:45:04.810 --> 00:45:06.373
There was Willis Lamb.

00:45:07.882 --> 00:45:10.573
It was just this star-studded faculty.

00:45:11.420 --> 00:45:13.840
So, the graduate students would, you know,

00:45:13.840 --> 00:45:15.440
feel a little bit awkward about this,

00:45:15.440 --> 00:45:16.307
so we got this nice button

00:45:16.307 --> 00:45:18.770
that said Not Yet, which
