00:46:21.880 --> 00:46:25.000
What you learned there was a
sense of wonder in physics,

00:46:25.000 --> 00:46:28.600
that you learn something,
and it's just beautiful.

00:46:28.600 --> 00:46:33.130
That, in fact, was a comment made to me

00:46:35.260 --> 00:46:38.910
some time ago by my senator in Illinois,

00:46:38.910 --> 00:46:41.830
who's now the president
of the United States.

00:46:41.830 --> 00:46:46.140
We had a conversation on physics.

00:46:46.140 --> 00:46:48.023
He seemed to know a lot about it.

00:46:49.396 --> 00:46:50.910
And what he said to me was amazing to me.

00:46:50.910 --> 00:46:54.790
He said, the thing about
science, and especially physics,

00:46:54.790 --> 00:46:58.210
he says, is when you
guys make a discovery,

00:46:58.210 --> 00:47:01.120
it turns out to be beautiful.

00:47:01.120 --> 00:47:04.300
Now, that was a surprise,

00:47:04.300 --> 00:47:08.440
because to say something
in physics is beautiful

00:47:08.440 --> 00:47:10.520
is something that
physicists say all the time,

00:47:10.520 --> 00:47:13.350
but not when outsiders
are listening, you know?

00:47:13.350 --> 00:47:16.180
You don't want to be bragging (laughs)

00:47:16.180 --> 00:47:18.330
about the fact that the
subject was beautiful.

00:47:18.330 --> 00:47:21.220
But here was a layperson, in a sense,

00:47:21.220 --> 00:47:25.370
who recognized the beauty of science.

00:47:25.370 --> 00:47:28.490
So, I'm very happy about
having him in the White House

00:47:28.490 --> 00:47:32.460
to care, hopefully at some point

00:47:33.500 --> 00:47:35.870
supporting the increases

00:47:36.870 --> 00:47:41.440
that he really understands
we need in research

00:47:41.440 --> 00:47:45.270
and education, which is
what we're all devoted to.

